###Rewriting $2^{x}$

$\begin{align}
2^{x} &= 2^{^{12 \cdot \scriptsize\dfrac{x}{12}}} & \normalsize\text{since } x=\dfrac{12x}{12}
\\\\
&= (2^{12})^{^{\scriptsize\dfrac{x}{12}}}  & \normalsize \text{since }k^{b \cdot c} = (k^b)^{c}
\end{align}$

###Rewriting $\left(\dfrac{1}{7}\right)^{x}$

$\begin{align}
\left(\dfrac{1}{7}\right)^{x} &= \left(\dfrac{1}{7}\right)^{^{-\scriptsize\dfrac19 \cdot -9x}} & \normalsize\text{since } x=\dfrac{-9x}{-9}
\\\\
&= \left(\left(\dfrac{1}{7}\right)^{^{-\scriptsize\dfrac19}} \right)^{-9x }  & \normalsize \text{since }k^{b \cdot c} = (k^b)^{c}
\end{align}$
